Before making any changes to this project:

1. Read CLAUDE.md in the project root completely.
2. Check docs/plans/ for the active plan document. Plan files use the
   pattern `<topic>_<YYYY-MM-DD>.md` and the most recent dated plan
   covering the area you're touching is authoritative.
3. Make focused, single-layer changes. Do not modify multiple layers
   in one commit. Layer boundaries are defined in CLAUDE.md.
4. Run py_compile on any file you modify before finishing.
5. Run the relevant package's test suite after the change.
6. After completing a change, remind the user to review git diff. Do
   not commit without explicit user instruction.

If you are unsure about anything, stop and ask.
